text: Dominique Dawes (born November 20, 1976 in Silver Spring, Maryland) is a retired gymnastics performer. She won multiple medals. As a member of the US National Gymnastic Team, she won a gold medal at the 1996 Summer Olympics."Team Gold for Dawes Was Only Part of Plan" Christopher Clarey, The New York Times, July 28, 1996 She was a ten year member of US National Gymnastic Team. ==References== Category:1976 births Category:Living people Category:Olympic gold medalists for the United States Category:American gymnasts Category:Olympic bronze medalists for the United States Category:People from Silver Spring, Maryland
